What is the sum of all integers $x$ in the interval shown ($0\le x\le 8$) such that $h(x)>x$ ?

solution:
We could check $h(x)$ separately for each integer $x$ from $0$ to $8$: for example, $h(0)\approx 3.8$, so $h(0)>0$, but $h(1)\approx -0.7$, so $h(1)\not>1$, and so on.

However, it is easier to see at a glance which $x$ satisfy $h(x)>x$ by superimposing a graph of $y=x$ on the graph of $y=h(x)$:

[asy]
draw((-0.75,-0.75)--(8.25,8.25),red+1);
